    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the established regulatory standard for this device class and the single test condition is consistent with FDA precedent. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework reliably predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated pedicle screw construct.",
